class Solution {
    public int minPartitions(String n) {
        int maxDigit = 0;
        for (char c : n.toCharArray()) {
            maxDigit = Math.max(maxDigit, c - '0');
        }
        return maxDigit;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through each character in the string once, finding the maximum digit which directly corresponds to the minimum number of deci-binary numbers needed to sum up to n.

